  "abstract": "Aflatoxin contamination seriously affects the edible quality of groundnuts and its\r\nproducts rendering them unfit for human and livestock consumption. Various surveys\r\nconducted in different parts of India have shown high aflatoxin levels in groundnut food\r\nproducts ( Gewande,1997). Terminal droughts are often a predisposing factor for aflatoxin\r\ncontamination in groundnut. In the present study the genotypic variation in aflatoxin\r\ncontamination under terminal moisture stress is examined",
